## Experiments and Commands

### 1. Read packets from network interface

```bash
sudo snort -i eth0 -A console
```

### 2. Read packets from a PCAP file

```bash
sudo snort -r file.pcap -A console
```

### 3. Test Snort Configuration

```bash
sudo snort -T -c /etc/snort/snort.conf
```

### 4. Capture and write packets

```bash
sudo snort -i eth0 -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -l .
```

### 5. Create a simple test rule

```bash
alert icmp any any -> any any (msg:"ICMP Test"; sid:1000001;)
```

### 6. Print alerts to console

```bash
sudo snort -A console -q -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
```

### 7. Limit traffic inspection

```bash
sudo snort -i eth0 -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -A console -n 10
```

### 8. Perform scanning using nmap

```bash
nmap -sS <target_ip>
```

### 9. Detect scan attacks

Add rules for:

* SYN scan
* UDP scan
* FIN scan
* NULL scan
* XMAS scan
  (in `local.rules`)

### 10. Run Snort in IDS mode

```bash
sudo snort -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
```

### 11. Detect ICMP to 8.8.8.8

Rule:

```bash
alert icmp any any -> 8.8.8.8 any (msg:"ICMP to Google DNS"; sid:1000002;)
```

Run:

```bash
sudo snort -i eth0 -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -A console
```

### 12. Detect HTTP GET request

```bash
alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"HTTP GET"; content:"GET"; sid:1000003;)
```

### 13. Detect suspicious User-Agent

```bash
alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"Suspicious UA"; content:"curl"; sid:1000011;)
```

### 14. Detect SQL Injection attempt

```bash
alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"SQL Injection"; content:"' OR 1=1"; sid:1000012;)
```

### 15. Detect suspicious DNS query

```bash
alert udp any any -> any 53 (msg:"DNS Query"; content:"malicious"; sid:1000013;)
```

